10/10/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- State Minister Mehmet Ali Sahin met Thursday (9 October) with a US congressional delegation led by Representative Jim Saxton. 
During their meeting, the officials agreed that the priority in Iraq is meeting the humanitarian needs of civilians. 
Saxton said stability can be restored only after humanitarian issues are settled. 
Earlier this week, parliament agreed to deploy Turkish peacekeepers in Iraq, as Washington had requested.
In other news Thursday, the ministerial meeting of the Mediterranean Forum began in Antalya. 
The 11-member forum will discuss measures to prevent organised crime, weapons smuggling, money laundering, and international terrorism. 
(Anadolu Agency, TRT 2, NTV - 09/10/03)
